{# 1. HERO — near-black, symptom headline with the italic accent phrase #}
<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero__inner">
    <h1 class="hero__headline">You do good work. You have the reviews. <span class="hero__phrase">Why can&rsquo;t people find you on Google?</span></h1>
    <p class="hero__sub">The {{ offer.price }} Deep Dive digs into your listings, reviews, rankings, and website — using nothing but your business name and city — and shows you the specific, checkable things costing you calls.</p>
    <div class="hero__actions">
      <a class="button" href="/deep-dive/">Get your Deep Dive</a>
      <a class="hero__sample-link" href="/sample/">See a real sample first &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# 2. PROBLEM — 3 cards, light #}
<section class="problem">
  <div class="problem__inner">
    <h2 class="section-heading">What&rsquo;s quietly costing you calls</h2>
    <div class="problem__cards">
      <article class="card">
        <h3 class="card__title">Three different addresses</h3>
        <p class="card__body">Your listings don&rsquo;t agree — three addresses, three ZIP codes across the web. Search engines can&rsquo;t pin down your identity, so they show a business they can be sure about instead.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3 class="card__title">A competitor above you</h3>
        <p class="card__body">The top of the page for your own service — sometimes the searchable version of your own name — belongs to someone else. Every customer who looks gets handed to them.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3 class="card__title">Your site says &ldquo;0 jobs&rdquo;</h3>
        <p class="card__body">Broken counters render as &ldquo;0+ installs, 0+ reviews&rdquo; — your own homepage advertising that you&rsquo;ve completed nothing, to every visitor, all day.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# 3. HOW IT WORKS — 3 steps, serif numerals in accent #}
<section class="how">
  <div class="how__inner">
    <h2 class="section-heading">How it works</h2>
    <ol class="how__steps">
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step__num" aria-hidden="true">1</span>
        <h3 class="step__title">Tell us your business</h3>
        <p class="step__body">Name, city, website, phone — a 60-second form. No logins, no account access, ever.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step__num" aria-hidden="true">2</span>
        <h3 class="step__title">We dig into everything</h3>
        <p class="step__body">Listings, reviews, rankings, your website, your competitors — every finding real and checkable, pulled from what search engines and your customers actually see.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step__num" aria-hidden="true">3</span>
        <h3 class="step__title">You get the report</h3>
        <p class="step__body">A written Deep Dive on your business: what&rsquo;s costing you calls, why, and what fixing it looks like.</p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

{# 3b. RESEARCH — why $39 can be deep. Claim ceiling per PROJECT_MASTER: automated
   research on public data, human pass on every report. No algorithm/monitoring claims. #}
<section class="research">
  <div class="research__inner">
    <h2 class="research__hook">Search engines don&rsquo;t read your website the way people do. We built something that reads it the way they do.</h2>
    <p class="research__body">A consultant charges hundreds because this takes a day of manual digging. AI does that digging in minutes — which is why a real, specific report on your business costs {{ offer.price }} instead of $500. And every report still gets human eyes before it ships.</p>
  </div>
</section>

{# 4. SEE IT FIRST — deep navy band, the ONLY --color-navy-deep use #}
<section class="see-first">
  <div class="see-first__inner">
    <h2 class="section-heading see-first__heading">See it first</h2>
    <p class="see-first__body">We ran two real contractors through the Deep Dive — one with a neglected online presence, one polished and well-reviewed — and found real, money-costing problems on both. Read the actual report before you spend a dollar.</p>
    <a class="button" href="/sample/">Read the sample report</a>
  </div>
</section>

{# 5. PRICING — single card, accent BORDER (never fill/background) #}
<section class="pricing">
  <div class="pricing__inner">
    <h2 class="section-heading">One report. No subscription.</h2>
    <div class="pricing-card">
      <p class="pricing-card__price">{{ offer.price }}</p>
      <p class="pricing-card__anchor"><s>{{ offer.anchor }}</s> value</p>
      <p class="pricing-card__urgency">{{ offer.urgency }}</p>
      <a class="button" href="/deep-dive/">Get your Deep Dive</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

